Possessions: (2)<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(116)">The Pale Blade</a> x2  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Bidding: <br>
Bid 2.  You want to have the Prancing Pony out, but you do not want to go first.<br>
<br>
Adventure Deck:<br>
[1] The Prancing Pony = Aragorn puller<br>
[2] Weatherhills = 3 Twilight Tokens and -1 Twilight for Nazgul, but is a River.<br>
[3] Fordo&#8217;s Bedroom = Not a river.<br>
[4] Balin&#8217;s Tomb = No site 4s help either side for me, this one is neutral<br>
[5] The Bridge Of Khazad-dum = No choice<br>
[6] Galadriel&#8217;s Glade = not a forest<br>
[7] Anduin Confluence = Discards allies, stops bounders from protection Frodo<br>
[8] Shores of Nen Hithoel =  9 Twililight<br>
[9] Summit of Amon Hen = Draw a card for a each burden<br>
<br>
Free Peoples:<br>
If you win the bid, only move to site 2 (Unless you have Ulaire Nelya in your hand), you do not want a river at site three.  If you lose the bid and get Aragorn out go to site 3.  Use Athleas; Sleep, Caradhras; and Albert Dreary to cancel Thin and Stretched and Desperate Defense of the Ring.  Just keep up with them, do not let them pull away.  You rangers and archers can handle anything your opponent throws at you.  Use your pumpers to win key fights.  hiney oon as you get Boromir out use him to fight.  Aragorn can heal him and he is not overwhelmed until tripled.  If you can not get Boromir out use Arwen and after Arwen use Aragorn.  Gandalf should only fight as a last defense.  Use your archers to stop the Orcs from exerting in battle.  Questions That Need Answering allows you to get key cards fast.  Isildur*s Bane stops out of skirmish wounds.<br>
<br>
Shadow:<br>
The Nazgul are VERY powerful.  A 1st turn Witch-King with his Blade can kill Aragorn or Arwen.  Add burdens as fast as possible to get Dark Whispers into action.  Use Ulaire Nelya to make sure they do not get a site for A Ranger*s Versatility until site 7.  Make sure to kill their archers with Relentless Charge(s) before they get to site 7.  If Frodo puts on the ring make sure to make them pay for it with Twilight World and Return to Its Master.  Morgul Skulkers allow you to retrieve your Witch-King and other Nazgul cards from the discard pile.<br>
<br>
Just advance your fellowship with theirs and smash their Fellowship with your Nazgul.<br>
<br>
